The paper discusses methods for measuring science and improving the accuracy of comparisons between articles. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and computers and society (cs.CY). However, given the focus on bibliographic data and keyword co-usage, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
